transcript.text: Hello, thank you for joining us today.
I'm excited to introduce you to the enhanced e-mail notifications feature in our latest version of On Print Shop.
Till now, it was a hassle for the admin to create and manage e-mail notifications as they were positioned at different places.
However, in our new version, we've centralized the e-mail notification settings, making it easier than ever to manage all your e-mail notifications in one place.
To achieve this, we have created 2 new tabs, Order Status e-mail and Quote Status e-mail.
With these tabs, you now have the flexibility to create distinct e-mail templates for each status.
We've also redesigned the e-mail and SMS notification user interface to improve your overall navigation experience.
Let's take a closer look at the new Order update status.
By simply clicking on the Edit button, you can customize the status notification.
Here you have the freedom to update the status template as well as specify the sender and receiver e-mail addresses.
What's more, you can even effortlessly check store wise emails.
Simply click on the drop down menu to filter and manage the e-mail template store wise.
And one more feature that allows you to view feature specific emails, Just click on the drop down menu and select the desired category.
Whether it's for administrators, printers, customers or others.
If you'd like to learn more about these exciting enhancements and explore other features of On Print Shop, please visit our website or reach out to our dedicated support team.
Thank you for watching, and we look forward to helping you streamline your e-mail notifications with On Print Shop's new version.

ocr.text: Previously, there was only a single email template available for all orders, products, and quote statuses.
Different email templates for distinct statuses were not possible.
. In the current version, we have addressed this limitation by introducing two new tabs: "Order Status Email" and
These tabs allow users to create separate email templates for different statuses.
Customers now have the ability to customize the email template, including the option to overwrite it.
. They can also specify the sender and receiver email addresses according to their preferences.
Additionally, customers can manage the Notify option for both customers and administrators through the same
